After the Tuesday meeting at the White House, more optimism plans on a possible agreement on the issues raised during the session on the "Boytock Duck", with the ratification of the New START Pact.
But William Galston, of the Brookings Institution, warns that fruitful cooperation on the most pressing problems of the "call Duck" session will not necessarily lead to a better agreement between the two parties when the 112th Congress meets in January.
