What would be the cause of change?
Public opinion.
It is widely proven that, despite the spirit of the recent election, a majority of Americans always want to see both parties work together.
If the confrontation leads to an impasse, as in 1995, then both parties will carefully observe the response of the public.
Anyone who will be judged to be losing will have to change his mind and find compromises.
